H3.text: what is the name of the gap between two front teeth. diastema

A4.text: A diastema (pl. : diastemata, from Greek διάστημα, 'space') is a space or gap between two teeth.

A5.text: In humans, the term is most commonly applied to an open space between the upper incisors (front teeth).
